Here's a card component built with MCSS best practices:

## Card Component (Molecule)

### HTML
```html
<div class="c-card" typeof="mcs:Component" property="mcs:taxonomyLevel" content="mcs:Molecule" property="mcs:purpose" content="A reusable card with title, description, and action button">
  <div class="c-card__header" property="mcs:hasPart" resource="#card-title">
    <h3 class="c-card__title" id="card-title">Card Title</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="c-card__body">
    <p class="c-card__description">This is a description text for the card component. It provides context and information about the card's content.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="c-card__footer">
    <button class="c-button" data-state="default" typeof="mcs:Component" property="mcs:taxonomyLevel" content="mcs:Atom" property="mcs:purpose" content="Action button within card">
      <span class="c-button__label">Learn More</span>
    </button>
  </div>
</div>
```

### CSS
```css
/* Component Layer */
.c-card {
  background-color: var(--color-background-primary);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border-default);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-md);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  overflow: hidden;
  transition: box-shadow var(--transition-base);
}

.c-card:hover {
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
}

.c-card__header {
  padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-4) 0;
}

.c-card__title {
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
  font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
  font-size: var(--font-size-title);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
  line-height: var(--line-height-tight);
  margin: 0;
}

.c-card__body {
  padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-4);
  flex: 1;
}

.c-card__description {
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
  font-size: var(--font-size-body);
  line-height: var(--line-height-base);
  margin: 0;
}

.c-card__footer {
  padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
  border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-default);
  display: flex;
  justify-content: flex-end;
}

/* Button component (atom) */
.c-button {
  background-color: var(--color-background-brand);
  border: none;
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-sm);
  color: var(--color-text-on-brand);
  cursor: pointer;
  font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
  font-size: var(--font-size-body);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
  padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-4);
  transition: background-color var(--transition-fast);
}

.c-button:hover {
  background-color: var(--color-background-brand-hover);
}

.c-button[data-state="disabled"] {
  opacity: 0.5;
  cursor: not-allowed;
}

.c-button__label {
  display: inline-block;
}
```

### Layout Usage Example
```html
<div class="l-grid l-grid--3col">
  <div class="c-card">
    <!-- card content -->
  </div>
  <div class="c-card">
    <!-- card content -->
  </div>
  <div class="c-card">
    <!-- card content -->
  </div>
</div>
```

### Design Decisions

1. **No margin on root**: The `.c-card` component has no margin — spacing is handled by the layout layer (e.g., `l-grid`).

2. **Semantic structure**: Uses `__header`, `__body`, and `__footer` elements for clear separation of content zones.

3. **Flex layout**: The card uses `flex-direction: column` with `flex: 1` on the body to ensure the footer stays at the bottom regardless of content height.

4. **Token-driven**: All values use CSS custom properties — no magic numbers.

5. **RDFa annotations**: The card is marked as a Molecule with `mcs:hasPart` referencing the title element. The button is an Atom nested within.

6. **State management**: The button uses `data-state` for disabled state rather than a class modifier.

7. **Hover interaction**: The card elevates shadow on hover, and the button changes background — both use `data-mcs-interaction-type` for behavioral documentation.

Here's a complete navigation bar component built with the MCSS framework.

## HTML Component

```html
<nav class="l-container l-cluster" typeof="mcs:Component" property="mcs:taxonomyLevel" content="mcs:Molecule" property="mcs:purpose" content="Primary site navigation bar with logo and page links">
  <div class="l-cluster__inner c-navigation" data-state="default">
