## CSS

```css
/* Layout layer — controls external spacing and container */
.l-container {
  max-width: var(--container-max-desktop);
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 var(--space-4);
}

.l-cluster {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  padding: var(--space-3) 0;
}

/* Component layer — no margin on root */
.c-navigation {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  width: 100%;
  padding: var(--space-2) 0;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-default);
  background-color: var(--color-background-primary);
}

.c-navigation__logo {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  text-decoration: none;
}

.c-navigation__logo-image {
  height: 32px;
  width: auto;
}

.c-navigation__links {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--space-6);
  list-style: none;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}

.c-navigation__item {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
}

.c-navigation__link {
  font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
  font-size: var(--font-size-body);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
  text-decoration: none;
  padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-2);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-sm);
  transition: color var(--transition-fast), background-color var(--transition-fast);
}

.c-navigation__link:hover {
  color: var(--color-text-link-hover);
  background-color: var(--color-background-secondary);
}

.c-navigation__item[data-state="active"] .c-navigation__link {
  color: var(--color-text-link);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
  border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border-interactive);
}

/* Responsive: stack on mobile */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .l-cluster {
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .c-navigation__links {
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }
}
```

## Design Decisions

1. **Layout separation**: The outer `l-container` and `l-cluster` handle all external spacing (margin, padding). The `c-navigation` component itself has **no margin** — this follows the Golden Rule.

2. **Flexbox alignment**: `justify-content: space-between` naturally pushes the logo left and links right without hard-coded margins.

3. **Active state via `data-state`**: The current page link uses `data-state="active"` on the `<li>` — not a class modifier. This follows MCSS state management rules.

4. **Token-driven styling**: All values use `var(--token)` — no magic numbers. Colors, spacing, fonts, and borders all reference design tokens.

5. **Responsive behavior**: On mobile (≤768px), the layout stacks vertically with a gap, maintaining usability on small screens.

6. **RDFa annotations**: The navigation is typed as `mcs:Molecule` (composed of atoms: logo, links). Each link is an `mcs:Atom`. The purpose describes the component's role.

# Success Alert Component

## HTML

```html
<div 
  class="c-alert c-alert--success" 
  role="alert"
  typeof="mcs:Component"
  property="mcs:taxonomyLevel" content="mcs:Molecule"
  property="mcs:purpose" content="Success notification with dismiss functionality"
  data-mcs-interaction-type="click"
  data-mcs-consequence="Dismisses the alert"
  data-mcs-triggers-event="alert:dismiss"
  data-state="default"
>
  <span class="c-alert__icon" aria-hidden="true">
    <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none">
      <path d="M10 0C4.48 0 0 4.48 0 10s4.48 10 10 10 10-4.48 10-10S15.52 0 10 0zm-1 15l-5-5 1.41-1.41L9 12.17l6.59-6.59L17 7l-8 8z" fill="currentColor"/>
    </svg>
  </span>

  <div class="c-alert__content">
    <p class="c-alert__message">Operation completed successfully!</p>
  </div>

  <button 
    class="c-alert__dismiss" 
    aria-label="Dismiss alert"
    data-state="default"
  >
    <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
  </button>
</div>
```

## CSS

```css
/* Component Layer */
.c-alert {
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-start;
  gap: var(--space-3);
  padding: var(--space-4);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-md);
  border: 1px solid;
  font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
  font-size: var(--font-size-body);
  line-height: var(--line-height-base);
  /* NO margin — Golden Rule */
}

.c-alert--success {
  background-color: var(--color-background-success);
  border-color: var(--color-border-success);
  color: var(--color-text-success);
}

.c-alert__icon {
  flex-shrink: 0;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  color: var(--color-green-500);
}

.c-alert__content {
  flex: 1;
  min-width: 0;
}

.c-alert__message {
  margin: 0;
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
}

.c-alert__dismiss {
  flex-shrink: 0;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  width: 24px;
  height: 24px;
  padding: 0;
  border: none;
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-sm);
  background: transparent;
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  cursor: pointer;
  font-size: var(--font-size-title);
  line-height: 1;
  transition: background-color var(--transition-fast), color var(--transition-fast);
}

.c-alert__dismiss:hover {
  background-color: var(--color-gray-200);
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
}

.c-alert__dismiss:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--color-border-focus);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

/* State: Dismissed (applied via JS) */
.c-alert[data-state="closed"] {
  display: none;
}
```

## Design Decisions

1. **Molecule taxonomy**: The alert combines multiple atoms (icon, text, button) into a cohesive notification unit.

2. **Golden Rule compliance**: No margin on `.c-alert` root — spacing is handled by the parent layout component (e.g., `l-stack`).

3. **Success styling**: Uses semantic tokens (`--color-background-success`, `--color-border-success`, `--color-text-success`) for consistent theming.

4. **Dismiss interaction**: The close button uses `data-state` for visibility control (`data-state="closed"` hides the alert), following the state management convention.

5. **Accessibility**: 
   - `role="alert"` for screen reader announcement
   - `aria-label` on dismiss button
   - `aria-hidden="true"` on decorative icon
   - Focus-visible styles for keyboard navigation

6. **Token-driven**: All values reference CSS custom properties — no magic numbers.

7. **Usage example with layout**:
```html
<div class="l-stack" style="--l-stack-space: var(--space-4)">
  <div class="c-alert c-alert--success" role="alert">
    <!-- alert content -->
  </div>
</div>
```

