```

## Design Decisions

1. **Semantic HTML**: Uses `<table>`, `<thead>`, `<tbody>`, `<th>`, and `<td>` for proper accessibility and structure.

2. **Component Architecture**: The table is a molecule composed of atoms (cells, rows, badge). Each part follows the `c-table__element` naming convention.

3. **No Margin on Root**: The `c-table` component declares no margin — spacing is handled by a layout wrapper if needed.

4. **Token-Driven**: All values use CSS custom properties (`var(--space-*)`, `var(--color-*)`, `var(--font-*)`) — no magic numbers.

5. **Header Styling**: Uses `c-table__cell--header` modifier for distinct visual treatment (uppercase, smaller font, secondary color).

6. **Status Badge**: The Status column uses a `c-badge` atom with a `--success` modifier for the "Active" state, demonstrating component composition.

7. **State Management**: The table uses `data-state="default"` on the root, ready for future states like `loading` or `empty`.

8. **Accessibility**: `scope="col"` on header cells improves screen reader navigation.

Here's a toggle switch component built with MCSS, perfect for settings panels and preference controls.

## HTML Component

```html
<!-- Toggle Switch Component -->
<div 
  class="c-toggle"
  typeof="mcs:Component"
  property="mcs:taxonomyLevel" content="mcs:Atom"
  property="mcs:purpose" content="A binary on/off toggle switch for settings"
  data-mcs-interaction-type="toggle"
  data-mcs-consequence="Toggles a setting between on and off states"
  data-mcs-triggers-event="toggle:change"
  data-state="off"
  role="switch"
  aria-checked="false"
  tabindex="0"
>
  <div class="c-toggle__track">
    <div class="c-toggle__thumb"></div>
  </div>
  <label class="c-toggle__label">Enable notifications</label>
</div>
```

## CSS

```css
/* Layer: Component (c-*) */

.c-toggle {
  /* Root component — NO margin per Golden Rule */
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--space-3);
  cursor: pointer;
  user-select: none;
  outline: none;
  transition: opacity var(--transition-fast);
}

.c-toggle[data-state="disabled"] {
  opacity: 0.5;
  cursor: not-allowed;
  pointer-events: none;
}

.c-toggle:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--color-border-focus);
  outline-offset: 2px;
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-sm);
}

/* Track — the background pill */
.c-toggle__track {
  position: relative;
  width: 44px;
  height: 24px;
  background-color: var(--color-gray-300);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-full);
  transition: background-color var(--transition-base);
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.c-toggle[data-state="on"] .c-toggle__track {
  background-color: var(--color-brand-500);
}

.c-toggle[data-state="off"] .c-toggle__track {
  background-color: var(--color-gray-300);
}

/* Thumb — the circular knob */
.c-toggle__thumb {
  position: absolute;
  top: 2px;
  left: 2px;
  width: 20px;
  height: 20px;
  background-color: var(--color-white);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-full);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  transition: transform var(--transition-base);
}

.c-toggle[data-state="on"] .c-toggle__thumb {
  transform: translateX(20px);
}

.c-toggle[data-state="off"] .c-toggle__thumb {
  transform: translateX(0);
}

/* Label */
.c-toggle__label {
  font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
  font-size: var(--font-size-body);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-regular);
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
  line-height: var(--line-height-base);
  cursor: pointer;
}

.c-toggle[data-state="disabled"] .c-toggle__label {
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
}
```

## Usage Example with Layout

```html
<!-- Layout wrapper provides spacing — NOT the component -->
<div class="l-stack" style="--l-stack-space: var(--space-4)">
  <div class="c-toggle" data-state="on" role="switch" aria-checked="true">
    <div class="c-toggle__track">
      <div class="c-toggle__thumb"></div>
    </div>
    <label class="c-toggle__label">Dark mode</label>
  </div>

  <div class="c-toggle" data-state="off" role="switch" aria-checked="false">
    <div class="c-toggle__track">
      <div class="c-toggle__thumb"></div>
    </div>
    <label class="c-toggle__label">Email notifications</label>
  </div>

  <div class="c-toggle" data-state="disabled" role="switch" aria-checked="false">
    <div class="c-toggle__track">
      <div class="c-toggle__thumb"></div>
    </div>
    <label class="c-toggle__label">Premium feature (upgrade required)</label>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Design Decisions

1. **State via `data-state`**: Uses `on`, `off`, and `disabled` states — no class modifiers. The `aria-checked` attribute mirrors the state for accessibility.

2. **Golden Rule compliance**: The `c-toggle` root has no margin. External spacing is handled by the layout wrapper (`l-stack`).

3. **Token-driven**: All values use CSS custom properties — no magic numbers. The thumb translation uses `20px` (track width 44px - thumb width 20px - 2px padding on each side = 20px offset).

4. **Accessibility**: Uses `role="switch"`, `aria-checked`, `tabindex="0"`, and `focus-visible` styling. The label is clickable via the `for`/`id` relationship (or wrapping).

5. **Interaction model**: The `data-mcs-interaction-type="toggle"` and `data-mcs-triggers-event="toggle:change"` enable event-driven architecture. JavaScript would listen for click/keyboard events and toggle `data-state` between `on`/`off`.

6. **Smooth animation**: The track background and thumb position both transition smoothly using `var(--transition-base)` for a polished feel.
